Services

DynamicPortForwarding

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicPortForwarding
This service provides functionality to manage dynamic port forwarding rule and dynamic IPv6 connection rule.

Actions

AddDynamicIPv6ConnectionRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicIPv6ConnectionRule
This action adds a dynamic IPv6 connection rule. It returns a ruleId which identifies the dynamic IPv6 connection rule.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
rule DynamicIPv6ConnectionRule no Dynamic IPv6 connection rule.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
ruleUUID UUID no rule UUID identifies a dynamic IPv6 connection rule.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicIPv6ConnectionRuleResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorDescriptionTooLong The specified description was longer than the maximum allowed length.
ErrorInvalidExternalPort One of the specified ports was not between 0 and 65535.
ErrorInvalidExternalPortRange One of the specified port ranges contained a first value that was greater than its last value.
ErrorRuleAlreadyExist The rule specified for the IPv6 connection already exists
ErrorSessionDoesNotExist The specified session does not exit.
ErrorTooManyRules Can not add this rule since the number of existing rules is already the maximum number of rules allowed.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicIPv6ConnectionRule"

{
  "rule": {
    "isEnabled": true,
    "srcIPv6Address": "2001:0DB8:85A3:0000:0000:8A2E:0370:7334",
    "firstExternalPort": 6888,
    "lastExternalPort": 6900,
    "destIPv6Address": "FE80:0000:0000:0000:20D0:58FF:FE73:4CF1",
    "description": "Twonky Media Server",
    "sessionUUID": "7e04d3bb-8789-4d6b-b8d1-d9b070dfe24e"
  }
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "ruleUUID": "1d0a3262-3cdf-42e5-a9b0-1481f790055f"
  }
}

AddDynamicPortRangeForwardingRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicPortRangeForwardingRule
This action adds a dynamic port range forwarding rule. It returns a ruleId which identifies the dynamic port forwarding rule.

Note:

This action is safe to call within the context of a transaction.

Input Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
rule DynamicPortRangeForwardingRule no Dynamic port range forwarding rule.

Output Parameters

Name Type Optional Description
ruleUUID UUID no rule UUID identifies a dynamic port range forwarding rule.

Result

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicPortRangeForwardingRuleResult
Value Description
OK Success.
Error
ErrorDescriptionTooLong The specified description was longer than the maximum allowed length.
ErrorInvalidExternalPort One of the specified external ports was not between 0 and 65535.
ErrorInvalidExternalPortRange The specified first external port was greater than the specified last external port.
ErrorInvalidInternalServerIPAddress The specified internal server IP address was invalid.
ErrorRuleAlreadyExist The rule specified for the dynamic port range forwarding already exists.
ErrorSessionDoesNotExist The specified session does not exit.
ErrorTooManyRules Can not add this rule since the number of existing rules is already the maximum number of rules allowed.
_ErrorAbortedAction
_ErrorInvalidInput
_ErrorInvalidOutput
_ErrorNotReady
_ErrorSessionVerification
_ErrorUnauthorized
_ErrorUnexpected
_ErrorUnknownAction
_ErrorUnknownSession

Sample Transaction

POST [request-uri] HTTP/1.1
Host: 192.168.1.1
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in request body]
X-JNAP-Action: "http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/AddDynamicPortRangeForwardingRule"

{
  "rule": {
    "isEnabled": true,
    "srcIPAddress": "172.26.223.18",
    "firstExternalPort": 6888,
    "lastExternalPort": 6900,
    "protocol": "Both",
    "internalServerIPAddress": "192.168.1.150",
    "description": "Twonky",
    "sessionUUID": "7e04d3bb-8789-4d6b-b8d1-d9b070dfe24e"
  }
}
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: [number of octets in response body]

{
  "result": "OK",
  "output": {
    "ruleUUID": "1d0a3262-3cdf-42e5-a9b0-1481f790055f"

Structures

DynamicIPv6ConnectionRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicIPv6ConnectionRule
A rule describing port/protocol combinations that should be dynamicly allowed to reach a specified IPv6 address on the LAN through the firewall. Only one rule can exist for a specific port/protocol combination at any given time.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
isEnabled bool no Whether the rule is enabled. Currently only true is accepted
srcIPv6Address IPv6Address no The IPv6 address of source which requests dynamic IPv6 connection.
firstExternalPort int no The first external port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535.
lastExternalPort int no The last external port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535. lastExternalPort >= firstExternalPort.
destIPv6Address IPv6Address no The IPv6 address of the desination for which the traffic should be allowed.
description string no A human-readable description of the rule.
sessionUUID UUID yes A session UUID which associates with the rule.

DynamicIPv6ConnectionRuleInfo

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicIPv6ConnectionRuleInfo
Information about a dynamic IPv6 connection rule info.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
ruleUUID UUID no A rule UUID identifies a dynamic IPv6 connection.
rule DynamicIPv6ConnectionRule no Dynamic IPv6 connection rule.

DynamicPortRangeForwardingRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicPortRangeForwardingRule
A rule describing a range of ports associated with a src IPv4 IPAddress that should be forwarded to a server on the LAN. Only one rule can exist for a specific external srcIPAddress/portRange/protocal combination at any given time.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
isEnabled bool no Whether the rule is enabled. Currently only true is accepted
srcIPAddress IPAddress no The IP address of source which requests dynamic port range forwarding.
firstExternalPort int no The first external port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535.
lastExternalPort int no The last external port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535. lastExternalPort >= firstExternalPort
protocol IPProtocol no The protocol that should be forwarded.
internalServerIPAddress IPAddress no The IP address of the destination server on the LAN. This value must be in the same subnet as the router's LAN host address (as defined by SetLANSettings), but not equal to the router's LAN host address and not fall inside the following reserved IP Addresses: 192.168.1.0 or 192.168.1.255
description string no A human-readable description of the rule.
sessionUUID UUID yes A session UUID identifies a dynamic session which the rule belongs to.

DynamicPortRangeForwardingRuleInfo

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicPortRangeForwardingRuleInfo
Information about an active dynamic port range forwarding rule.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
ruleUUID UUID no A rule UUID identifies a dynamic port forwarding rule.
rule DynamicPortRangeForwardingRule no Dynamic port range forwarding rule.

DynamicSinglePortForwardingRule

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicSinglePortForwardingRule
A rule describing a single-port associated with a src IPv4 IPAdress that should be forwarded to a port in a server on the LAN. Only one rule can exist for a specific external srcIPAddress/port/protocol combination at any given time.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
isEnabled bool no Whether the rule is enabled. Currently only true is accepted
srcIPAddress IPAddress no The IP address of source which requests dynamic single-port forwarding.
externalPort int no The first external port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535.
protocol IPProtocol no The protocol that should be forwarded.
internalServerIPAddress IPAddress no The IP address of the destination server on the LAN. This value must be in the same subnet as the router's LAN host address (as defined by SetLANSettings), but not equal to the router's LAN host address and not fall inside the following reserved IP Addresses: 192.168.1.0 or 192.168.1.255
internalPort int no The first internal port in the range that should be forwarded. This value must be between 0 and 65535.
description string no A human-readable description of the rule.
sessionUUID UUID yes A session UUID identifies a dynamic session which the rule belongs to.

DynamicSinglePortForwardingRuleInfo

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/DynamicSinglePortForwardingRuleInfo
Information about an active dynamic single-port forwarding rule.

Structure Members

Member Name Type Optional Description
ruleUUID UUID no A rule UUID identifies a dynamic port forwarding rule.
rule DynamicSinglePortForwardingRule no Dynamic single-port forwarding rule

Enumerations

IPProtocol

http://linksys.com/jnap/dynamicportforwarding/IPProtocol
IP protocols.

Enumeration Values

Value Description
TCP The TCP protocol.
UDP The UDP protocol.
Both Both the TCP and UDP protocols.
